{
  "text": "Analogous results to eqs. (1.8) and (1.9) were found by a different approach in [CITATION_1] for the Wiener sausage in dimensions d \u2265 4. To show eq. (1.7) we utilize a refined version of the decomposition eq. (1.5) to represent V t as a sum of i.i.d. random variables which we then approximate with a Brownian motion according to the Skorohod embedding theorem.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "123113994"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "123113994": {
      "title": "Laws of the iterated logarithm for high-dimensional Wiener sausage",
      "abstract": "Let {\u03b2(s), s \u2265 0} be the standard Brownian motion in \u211d d with d \u2265 4 and let |W r (t)| be the volume of the Wiener sausage associated with {\u03b2(s), s \u2265 0} observed until time t. From the central limit theorem of Wiener sausage, we know that when d \u2265 4 the limit distribution is normal. In this paper, we study the laws of the iterated logarithm for \\(\\left| {W_r (t)} \\right| - \\mathbb{E}\\left| {W_r (t)} \\right|\\) in this case."
    }
  }
}